---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Efficient Machine Learning | Harutyun Harry Ilanyan">
  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Quantized LLM Performance Benchmarking</h1>
    
    <div class="alert alert-info mb-8">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="stroke-current shrink-0 w-6 h-6">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
      </svg>
      <span>This project is currently in progress. More details will be added as the research develops.</span>
    </div>

    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>
      This project focuses on comprehensive evaluation of 2-bit and 4-bit quantization techniques on large language models using GPTQ and AWQ methods. 
      The research includes detailed analysis of performance degradation and optimization strategies to make AI systems more accessible and computationally efficient.
    </p>

    <h2>Research Objectives</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Evaluate performance of quantization techniques on various LLM architectures</li>
      <li>Analyze the trade-offs between model compression and performance quality</li>
      <li>Develop optimization strategies for efficient deployment</li>
      <li>Benchmark against industry-standard evaluation metrics</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Technical Stack</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6 not-prose">
      <div class="badge badge-primary">Python</div>
      <div class="badge badge-secondary">PyTorch</div>
      <div class="badge badge-accent">GPTQ</div>
      <div class="badge badge-info">AWQ</div>
      <div class="badge badge-success">Quantization</div>
      <div class="badge badge-warning">LLM</div>
      <div class="badge badge-error">Benchmarking</div>
    </div>

    <h2>Current Status</h2>
    <p>
      The project is currently in the development phase, with ongoing experiments in model quantization and performance evaluation. 
      Stay tuned for updates on preliminary results and findings.
    </p>

    <div class="flex gap-4 mt-8 not-prose">
      <a href="/projects" class="btn btn-outline">‚Üê Back to Projects</a>
      <a href="mailto:harry_ila@berkeley.edu" class="btn btn-primary">Contact for Collaboration</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>